cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for clustering words based on their semantic similarity. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses spectral clustering and graph cut algorithms, which are common in machine learning and data mining, suggesting that it could also fit into cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses distributional representations of words, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates its results against a dataset of human judgments, which suggests it could fit into cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
